{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5985bea7-f0ba-4650-99c5-cd1d78dcd067","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x removed the VSTest compatibility bridge by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK shipped with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge`, so `vstest.console` could still discover and run tests. In 4.x, that bridge is gone — the project exclusively targets **Microsoft.Testing.Platform**.\n\n### Your options\n\n**Option A (recommended):** Switch your CI to use `dotnet test`, which now invokes Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n**Option B (quick fix):** Re-enable the VSTest bridge in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Option C:** Run the test executable directly, since Microsoft.Testing.Platform builds a self-contained test host:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nOption A is the recommended migration path — `vstest.console` is being phased out in favor of the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0eeca743-4a69-4c5a-bf0c-e14e9966cae0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the SDK used Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default but still supported the VSTest protocol. In MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed by default.\n\nSpecifically, in MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the property `EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage` and the VSTest bridge (`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge`) were included by default. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the VSTest bridge is no longer included by default, meaning `vstest.console.exe` can no longer discover or run these tests.\n\n\nThe breaking change is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x removed the VSTest compatibility bridge by default, so projects relying on `vstest.console.exe` or the VSTest runner won't discover tests anymore. To fix this, you can either revert to the VSTest infrastructure with a configuration flag, add the VSTest bridge extension back, or migrate to using `dotnet test` with the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner, which is the recommended approach going forward. Let me wrap this up with a clear summary of the solution.","outputTokens":788,"requestId":"A045:33188C:1E2CCD1:2258C90:69FEA4CB"},"id":"cd069367-7255-4c93-a154-62f4b17d5245","timestamp":"2026-05-09T03:07:08.439Z","parentId":"802cce61-494f-4f4e-ad8e-c51ee2debe0a"}
